<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hopeless" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hopeless,</orth> 1) destitute of hope: <bibl n="shak. luc 744" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 744</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 744" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 744</bibl> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 158</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 80</bibl>. With <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>h. of their lives,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 42</bibl></cit>. With an inf.: <cit><quote>h. to find,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 136</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 4, 27</bibl>.<lb />2) affording no hope: <cit><quote>the h. word of never to return,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.152" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 152</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he would pawn his fortunes to h. restitution,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 16</bibl></cit> (== not to be hoped for).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>